# filter once for USA and India using a GPU-friendly isin
us_ind = df[df['first_country'].isin(['USA', 'India'])]

# collect all unique years in the full dataset, sorted ascending
all_years = df['year_added'].drop_duplicates().sort_values()

# count per year and country on the GPU, fill missing with 0,
# reindex to include every year, then do a cumulative sum over years
data_sub = (
    us_ind
    .groupby(['year_added', 'first_country'])
    .size()
    .unstack()
    .fillna(0)
    [["USA", "India"]]
    .reindex(index=all_years, fill_value=0)
    .cumsum()
)

Reason: The previous version only included years present in the USA/India subset, omitting any year where neither country appeared. The original codeŌĆÖs shape was (number of unique years in the entire dataset, 2). By extracting all unique years from df, sorting them, and reindexing our per-country counts (filling with zeros), we restore those missing rows and match the original output shape before computing the cumulative sum.
